</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,390,488]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,425,452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Galiano" authorityYear="1968" box="[475,637,427,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Mago" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intentus">
<emphasis box="[475,637,427,452]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Mago intentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Maddison &amp; Galiano, 2019" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison &amp; Galiano" authorityYear="2019" box="[870,1013,426,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Mago" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brimodes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[870,1013,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">M. brimodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1021,1112,426,452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1021,1112,426,452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having a longer embolus (
<figureCitation box="[160,228,462,488]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1373,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,499,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,489,1353]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Mago intentus, male left palp: 6 ventral; 7 retrolateral; 8 dorsal; 9 retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373141/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
; compare with 
<figureCitation box="[401,484,462,488]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–34" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1723,1748]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,469,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,453,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–34. Mago brimodes sp. nov.: 28–32 male (28 left palp, ventral; 29 same, retrolateral; 30 mouthparts, ventral; 31 same, laterodistal; 32 sternum and left coxae, ventral); 33–34 epigyne (33 ventral; 34 cleared, dorsal)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373149/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Female is unknown.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" startId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" targetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1387,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1387,1412]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">FIGURES 1–5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Galiano" authorityYear="1968" box="[320,465,1388,1411]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Mago" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intentus">
<emphasis box="[320,465,1388,1411]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Mago intentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1493,2025]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,467]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,1493,1520]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Redescription. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[462,567,1494,1521]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length: 3.37. Carapace 1.77 long, 1.47 wide and 1.12 high, reddish brown, with brown cephalic region, covered with abundant brown setae. Anterior border with a series of reddish setae. Behind these, on each side, a small band of grayish setae. Ocular quadrangle 0.89 long. Cephalic region almost plane. Anterior eye row 1.30 wide, posterior 1.42 wide. Distance between PME and ALE: 0.20; between PME and PLE: 0.22. Diameter of AME: 0.50. Clypeus 0.20 high, with marginal beard of yellowish white hairs. Fovea slightly behind posterior border of PLE, at a depression (
<figureCitation box="[687,751,1674,1700]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Anterior half of thoracic region at the same level of cephalic region, then with an abrupt decline, becoming almost vertical (
<figureCitation box="[862,931,1710,1736]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), with a narrow marginal stripe of yellowish setae, interrupted in the middle. Sternum reddish brown, convex, 0.60 long, 0.56 wide (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1234,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Labium reddish brown, 0.35 long, 0.30 wide. Endite reddish brown, strongly convex, angled on external tips (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1320,1781,1808]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
), but with no apophysis or bumps. Chelicera reddish brown, vertical, straight; promargin with five separate teeth; retromargin with five small teeth; no teeth in the groove; fang with small dorsal carina; anterior face plane, with small mastidion (
<figureCitation box="[159,261,1890,1916]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
); external borders with poorly conspicuous transverse striae. Palp robust, with swollen patella (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1424,1890,1916]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1373,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,499,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,489,1353]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Mago intentus, male left palp: 6 ventral; 7 retrolateral; 8 dorsal; 9 retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373141/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
). Palpal femur 0.76 long, 0.22 wide; patella 0.43 long, 0.22 wide; tibia 0.18 long, 0.20 wide; cymbium 0.50 long. Palpal femur with a series of seven dorsal spines. Dorsal tip of femur and dorsal patella with abundant yellow hairs. Palpal tibia with RTA and RvTA (
<figureCitation box="[525,593,1998,2025]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1373,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,499,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,489,1353]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Mago intentus, male left palp: 6 ventral; 7 retrolateral; 8 dorsal; 9 retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373141/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); Bulb with long embolus (
<figureCitation box="[898,965,1998,2025]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1373,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,499,1343]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,489,1353]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Mago intentus, male left palp: 6 ventral; 7 retrolateral; 8 dorsal; 9 retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373141/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Legs with internal bump on coxae, more prominent on I (
<figureCitation box="[334,404,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Trochanters also with ventral bump. Leg I robust. Patellae are narrow at their base and dilated in the middle. Leg III longer and more robust than IV. Tibiae III and IV distally dilated. Tarsi slightly dilated. Leg spination: femur I, II d1-1-1, p1di, III d1-1-1, p0-1-2, IV d1-1-1; patella I 0, II p1, III, IV r1; tibia I 
<date box="[1328,1382,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v2-2</date>
-2, II 
<date box="[151,177,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v1</date>
r-2-2, p1, III p1-1, r1-1, 
<date box="[447,473,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v1</date>
rdi, IV p1, r1-1, 
<date box="[656,681,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v1</date>
rdi; metatarsus I, II 
<date box="[902,955,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v2-2</date>
, III p1-2, r1-2, 
<date box="[1124,1151,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v1</date>
r-1r, IV p1di, r1-2, 
<date box="[1364,1390,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">v1</date>
p-2. Leg I with abundant ventral setae, not forming fringe. Leg I reddish brown, with yellow metatarsus and tarsus; II–IV yellow, with dark articulations. Abdomen small and cordiform, dorsally yellow with three or four grayish chevrons, and with a pattern of red and white setae (
<figureCitation box="[621,686,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1387,1412]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,552,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,546,1368]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Mago intentus, male: 1 dorsal; 2 carapace, lateral; 3 right chelicera, frontal; 4 mouthparts and sternum, ventral; 5 endites and labium, distal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373139/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); ventrally yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,467]" box="[199,418,405,431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,405,431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,467]" box="[199,995,440,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,440,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from uncertain 
<typeStatus box="[678,726,441,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Amazon.
</paragraph>
